---
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import SectionIntro from '../components/SectionIntro.astro';
import ExperienceCard from '../components/ExperienceCard.astro';
import ContactForm from '../components/ContactForm.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import lineArtTwo from '../assets/img/line-art-2.svg';
---

<BaseLayout>
  <Header />
  <main id="main-content">
    <Hero />

    <section id="when-to-bring-me-in" class="section section-soft">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <SectionIntro heading="When to bring me in" intro="Bring me in when:" />
        <ul class="clean-list">
          <li>the direction is not yet settled, but momentum is building</li>
          <li>options are contested and stakeholders are not yet aligned</li>
          <li>the investment case is forming, but the logic needs testing</li>
          <li>there is pressure to move, but readiness is still unclear</li>
          <li>the consequences of getting the next step wrong are material</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This is usually the point where independent advice adds most value: when the decision is live, the pressure is
          real, and the cost of a poor call will show up later.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="what-i-do" class="section">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <SectionIntro heading="What I actually do" />
        <div class="prose">
          <p>
            I provide independent advice when organisations need to decide what to do, why it stacks up, and whether the
            timing is right.
          </p>
          <p>
            The work usually involves clarifying the real decision, testing assumptions and investment logic, working
            through stakeholder complexity, and assessing sequencing, readiness and risk.
          </p>
          <p>
            I am brought in early enough to question the brief, sharpen the case, and reduce the risk of premature lock-in.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="experience" class="section section-soft">
      <div class="container">
        <SectionIntro heading="Selected experience" />
        <div class="experience-carousel" data-carousel>
          <div class="experience-controls" aria-label="Experience carousel controls">
            <button type="button" class="carousel-control" data-carousel-prev>Previous</button>
            <button type="button" class="carousel-control" data-carousel-next>Next</button>
          </div>
          <div class="experience-list" data-carousel-track>
            <ExperienceCard
              number={1}
              title="Local board advisory work"
              bodyOne="Commissioned by multiple Auckland local boards on fixed-scope sport and active recreation planning and access-related work."
              bodyTwo="The focus has been on helping decision-makers work through supply, demand, provision, investment priorities, advocacy priorities and local access questions before further commitments are made."
            />
            <ExperienceCard
              number={2}
              title="Public-sector systems and leasing decisions"
              bodyOne="Led cross-council work to improve the community leasing process so peppercorn leases could be used more effectively to deliver public and community benefit."
              bodyTwo="This involved balancing policy intent, sector input, implementation realities and competing priorities inside local government."
            />
            <ExperienceCard
              number={3}
              title="University recreation facility readiness"
              bodyOne="Worked within a major university recreation environment during facility transition, operational setup and business unit growth."
              bodyTwo="That created direct visibility into how early planning, design and investment decisions translate into operating reality once a facility opens."
            />
            <ExperienceCard
              number={4}
              title="National sport and system context"
              bodyOne="Worked across Sport New Zealand in roles spanning sport development, special projects and the ongoing development of the Balance is Better platform."
              bodyTwo="This provided strong exposure to how direction is formed within institutions, how priorities are interpreted across functions, and how national thinking is carried into the sector."
            />
            <ExperienceCard
              number={5}
              title="Major event readiness"
              bodyOne="Worked within the FIFA Women’s World Cup host city programme across training venue settings."
              bodyTwo="This meant operating in a setting where sequencing, coordination, readiness and public scrutiny all mattered under fixed deadlines."
            />
            <ExperienceCard
              number={6}
              title="Regional funding and programme scale"
              bodyOne="Led regional KiwiSport investment and helped scale the Good Sports programme from pilot to nationally recognised programme."
              bodyTwo="This built practical experience in how funding settings, programme design and stakeholder incentives shape behaviour and outcomes across a wider system. Good Sports later received national recognition for its impact."
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="about" class="section">
      <div class="container narrow about-grid">
        <div>
          <SectionIntro heading="About" />
          <div class="prose">
            <p>
              My experience spans Sport New Zealand, Auckland Council, Tātaki Auckland Unlimited, the University of
              Auckland and Aktive.
            </p>
            <p>
              Across those environments, the pattern has been consistent: important decisions are often made while
              assumptions are still weak, stakeholders are not fully aligned, and pressure to progress is stronger than the
              case for doing so.
            </p>
            <p>That is usually where I add most value.</p>
            <p>
              I now work independently, helping organisations make better decisions earlier, before commitments harden and
              before avoidable complexity becomes someone else’s problem.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="about-art" aria-hidden="true">
          <img src={lineArtTwo.src} alt="" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="contact" class="section section-soft">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <SectionIntro heading="Contact" intro="If you’re working through a decision like this, feel free to get in touch." />
        <ContactForm />
        <p class="contact-alt">
          Not a fan of forms? Email me directly at
          <a href="mailto:hamish@hmrsportsolutions.co">hamish@hmrsportsolutions.co</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const carousel = document.querySelector('[data-carousel]');
  const track = carousel?.querySelector('[data-carousel-track]');
  const prevButton = carousel?.querySelector('[data-carousel-prev]');
  const nextButton = carousel?.querySelector('[data-carousel-next]');

  if (track && prevButton && nextButton) {
    const reduceMotion = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)');

    const moveByCard = (direction) => {
      const card = track.querySelector('.experience-card');
      if (!card) return;
      const styles = window.getComputedStyle(track);
      const gap = Number.parseFloat(styles.columnGap || styles.gap || '0');
      const amount = card.getBoundingClientRect().width + gap;
      track.scrollBy({ left: direction * amount, behavior: reduceMotion.matches ? 'auto' : 'smooth' });
    };

    prevButton.addEventListener('click', () => moveByCard(-1));
    nextButton.addEventListener('click', () => moveByCard(1));
  }
</script>
